KW  - Autocorrelation
KW  - Durable goods
KW  - Moving average process
KW  - Permanent income hypothesis
AB  - This paper examines the time series behavior of durables/nondurables and services consumption expenditure of six OECD countries, following Caballero's approach. In each country, durables expenditure exhibits greater reversion than nondurables and services, when lower frequencies of the series are examined. The results reject the frictionless PIH as a model for durable goods consumption. However, they strongly support Mankiw's hypothesis on the nature of durable goods consumption.
