KW  - Demand system
KW  - Morishima elasticities
AB  - We estimate a dynamic asymptotically ideal model of a system of money demand equations. This specification allows incomplete portfolio adjustment. We base our policy conclusions on Morishima elasticities, because as Blackorby and Russell (1989) show, the Allen-Uzawa elasticities can give misleading results. We find that cash assets, savings deposits, and small time deposits are all substitutes for each other. These results imply that monetary authorities should target a relatively broad monetary aggregate that includes these assets, if policy is to have predictable effects on the economy.
ER  - 

